Harry stood before the bungalow in Grand Cove, hair neatly slicked back, the jacket they'd shared in a land beyond time hanging loose on his tensed-up shoulders.

He raised his hand to knock.

He lowered it.

He let his other hand linger at the doorknob for a few more seconds before turning and walking away, cheeks burning in the cold sunlight.

