[[div style="border:solid 1px #999999; background:#FFFFFF; padding-left: 16px; padding-right: 16px; margin-bottom: 16px; margin-top: 16px;"]]
The residential arrangements at Site-169 are much more varied than you'd find at any other Foundation facility, since it serves so many congregational purposes. There's single rooms for folks on solitary sick leave, group halls for overnight parties, double rooms for couples, linked suites to accommodate VIPs and their bodyguards, and of course private common room/single room combo blocks for team-building exercises. It is an open secret that some of these configurations feature open bars; proposals have been made annually to remove this feature, as it has been implicated in more than a few team-dismantling exercises, restraining orders, and marriages.

[[>]]
-- Dr. Harold Blank, "Succour, Champagne, Reflect: All Play and No Work at Site-169," in //Praeterita//, vol. 36 no. 2 (Summer 2004): 31-44.
[[/>]]
