++ 22 September
[[/=]]

----

Harry was face-first in a bowl of Lucky Charms when he heard one of the suite doors open, and raised his head to see Lillian wandering into the common room. She was wearing an extra-large Site-169 T-shirt like a dress, and nothing else. She looked like she'd just seen a ghost.

"Help." She flopped down into the chair beside his, and put her head in her hands.

He wiped off his beard. The single bowl of sugar had been his reward for losing fifteen pounds of fat, and vastly increasing his muscle mass so that he was almost what most active human beings would consider bog-average. "What?"

"I almost."

He put a hand on her shoulder. "You almost what?"

"Wettle." She burped. The scent of whiskey wafted over him.

"You almost Wettle?" he laughed.

She winced at the sound. //Hangover, then.// "Yeah."

"Well, you should've gone before we left."

She darted to her right and pinched his nipple, hard.

"Ow!" He slapped her hand away.

She grabbed his chin, and stared into his eyes. The first thing that came into his head was //seen some shit.// "I almost slept with Wettle," she breathed.

"Wow?" He wrinkled his nose. He was getting contact drunk off her fumes.

"What the fuck, Harry." She put her arms on the table, and buried her head in the crooks of her elbows.

"How much did you drink?"

"I didn't drink anything." She hiccoughed. "I drank //after.//"

"What?" He laughed. "Did you fall and hit your head or something?"

"It wasn't because it was Wettle. It was because my libido is swinging from the chandeliers."

"Oh." He nodded.

"Oh?" She looked up blearily.

"Yeah. Us too."

Her eyes narrowed. "Who us too?"

"Udo and I."

"You and Udo?"

"Yeah."

"Huh."

"What?"

She hid her face again. "Nothing."

It was the shots. It had to be. LeClair had declined to explain what was in them, but they'd all been feeling energized, sharper, friskier since the injections. Something to do with McInnis' promise of advanced Foundation healthcare, he supposed. Maybe even O5 shit. //Well, no harm done so far.//

Another door opened, and Del walked out in her tank top and shorts. From the look on her face, Harry expected her to say she'd found a corpse in her bed.

"I slept with Wettle," she whispered.

