++ 11 October
[[/=]]

----

They wandered into Bad Karlshafen two days later, clothes in tatters, battered and bruised and covered head to toe with dust. Their federal agent badges got them into the relief camp set up for the survivors of Site-06, which was presently a smoking ruin already described in the popular press as some kind of freak tectonic disaster. The Nature Conservation people were going to get to clamp down even harder on the region in response, which was good, because the whole facility would need to be written off and its inmates, the ones who'd been recaptured, relocated. 

Someone had managed to stop the nuclear device from going off. Smart money was on Wheeler and Lillihammer, though neither of them could remember doing it. Someone had also liberated two prisoners, and killed about two dozen members of Site security staff in the process. The former fact had to be added, re-added, and re-re-added to the official report by Wheeler, who was used to that kind of thing, as nobody but them seemed to remember that either Alis Rydderech or Imogen Tarrow had ever been incarcerated at Site-06, or in fact who those names might even belong to.

A comprehensive debriefing showed that neither memeticist nor antimemeticist remembered anything past midnight on the first day. Not how they'd survived. Not how they'd escaped. Not even what could have happened to make them forget these things. Even with Lillian's pluperfect recall, the information was simply gone.

Except the part about the vessel.

"So yeah, glass half full," she told Wheeler as the Day Trippers' Sea King landed to take them back to North America.

Wheeler again threatened to shoot her, without even saying a word.

