+ ##990011|2005##
++ 8 September
[[span style="font-family: BauhausLTDemi; font-size: 120%;"]]**[http://www.scpwiki.com/secure-facility-dossier-site-43 Site-43]: Lambton County, Ontario, Canada**[[/span]]
[[/=]]

----

Allan McInnis stared at his redline telephone. He knew the timeline; he had a counter ticking down on the computer monitor beside him. He was going to get this down to the second. It was perhaps the most time-sensitive element of the entire procedure.

He needed to be precisely as tardy as he'd been on the least effective day of his life.

When the tinnitus came, he ignored it. When the phone rang, he ignored it. He turned to glance at the timer, forcing himself to wait, as the rings rang out. Then started again.

At the exact moment he'd done so on September 8, 2002, he snatched up the redline receiver and barked: "McInnis. Report." It came out harsher than it had before. He had knowledge now which he hadn't had then, which he couldn't forget. He had changed in ways he could not keep out of his voice.

"We, we, we have multiple…" The man on the other end of the line, David Markey, sobbed in such a way as to suggest a theatre student approximating grief. It seemed that Markey's ghost, too, was going through the motions. He began to sing to himself.

"State your location," McInnis said kindly, sadly, "and situation."

"Hyperbolic. Hyperbolic. All of F-D is going up, sir. All at once."

//Good.//

"Set the breach alarm." He killed the connection, then dialled up Zulfikar. "S&C."

His secretary put the call through instantly.

"Gather every available agent. Listen very carefully."

"Go ahead, sir," said the ghost of Janet Gwilherm.

"Materials breach in F-D." He was staring at his painting now, lost in a trance. "Send a team to the main airlock. Nascimbeni's in charge."

"Yes, sir."

The line died, along with a small but significant portion of his soul.

