[[image http://scp-wiki.wdfiles.com/local--files/the-b-b-decommission/Asterisk43.png]]
@@ @@
[[/=]]

Ibanez leaned on the wall, arms crossed, eyes closed. She had watched the bullpen camera footage from September 8 very closely. She knew what she'd need to hear, and when she might expect to hear it.

She wasn't going to look until it was absolutely necessary.

She heard a squeak, as of a bullpen chair being leaned back, and a musical laugh. "That was just the short version! In full: Dr. William Wettle legitimately believes that D-class personnel are sold //en masse// to the Foundation by an anomalous smarmy salesman with a spray tan, who only shows up if you write a really wasteful experiment schedule."

Ibanez nodded, eyes still closed. "Thank god he's never gonna be responsible for anything important." She wondered how Wettle was coming along with the very important thing they had all been forced, against their better judgement, to trust him with.

There was a soft //ping,// then the sound of a button being depressed. Gwilherm began speaking to McInnis, and Ibanez let her focus drift until all she could hear was Charlie Brown adults warbling in the distance. //Almost done. You're almost done. It's fine.//

"Yes, sir," said Gwilherm, and Ibanez opened her eyes and leapt onto the intercom button. "You heard the man!" She pointed at each of the sacrificial lambs in turn, viciously, accusingly, and spoke their names aloud: "Radcliffe, Gwilherm, Mukami! Double time!"

They practically leapt to attention before rushing off. She hoped that wouldn't affect the outcome.

She //thought// she hoped it wouldn't affect the outcome.

