[[/=]]

Harry sat in the middle of the Salt Mines, staring at the space where the water cooler had been. Reuben Wirth's work station had been removed from storage and returned to its original, awkward location in the corner of two rows of desks. The papers he'd been working on at his time of death had been carefully filed on the event, and were now returned to their original location as well. It was coming up hard on six thirty, and Harry was waiting for the population of this deserted space to suddenly double.

He still wasn't sure it was really going to happen. Even knowing what he knew, it was a lot to imagine. He'd heard the testimony from the officers who'd seen Gwilherm, Radcliffe and Mukami pop back into existence, so he knew roughly what to expect, but whether or not it would happen again, after all they'd been through in the interim...

He'd been looking down at his console when the breach began, he recalled. So, he looked down at his console. He was checking citations for //Lines in a Muddle,// ahead of a possible first edition after all these years of plugging away. Dealing with history seemed entirely appropriate, given the circumstances...

//BOOM. BOOM. BOOM. BOOM. BOOM. BOOM. BOOM. BOOM. BOOM. BOOM. BOOM. BOOM. BOOM. BOOM.//

Fourteen booms. He said, on script, without looking up: "What was that?" It came out curiously flat.

And then he did look up.

Reuben Wirth was sitting at his desk -- Harry would later learn that he'd been sitting there for fifteen seconds before the BOOMs -- and looking out the glass wall windows to the hall without. "It sounded like a 'mech," the young man replied. He sounded like he thought he was in a dream. "Y'know, from //Battletech.//"

"If it's a 'mech..." Harry got that much of the quotation out without trouble, repeating his own words, but he faltered on the second half. Wirth hardly seemed to notice, standing up and heading for the door.

"Reuben..." It was all Harry could do not to reach out for the other man as he marched to his doom.

The door closed behind him.

"It'll stomp you flat."

