None of them felt very much like talking, but they were there. That was the important part. They were present, for each other.

"So," Nascimbeni sighed into his beer. 

"Yeah," Lillian agreed. "So this is our life now."

"Just one day a year," McInnis reminded her.

"//If// we do it right," Ibanez reminded him.

"So, we'll do it right." Udo nodded as if to confirm her own statement.

Harry laughed.

Wettle blinked stupidly at him. "What?"

"We're fucked."

