"What do these shots do?"

LeClair was taken aback. Ibanez hadn't thought to ask, the first time, she'd just assumed it was related to the life extension treatments they'd been promised. She'd been too embarrassed to bring it up the previous year, since the linked escalation of her sex drive had resulted in something so horrifically traumatic that she couldn't risk having to describe it out loud, not even to her doctor, not even months after the fact. This year, though, both the novelty and some of the pain had worn off.

LeClair shrugged, and drove the plunger home. "I don't know."

"What do you mean, you don't know?"

"The Council has indicated that these shots are safe for the seven of you to take, and that's all. I believe them, because you never hear about an O5 dropping dead." LeClair dropped the spent needle into an opaque black bag, completely ignoring the yellow sharps disposal bin on the wall beside her.

"You hear about them killing people all the time, though."

The older woman smirked. "Yes, well, //I// wouldn't take the shot. But that's your job, right?"

